This paper is about learning the structure of Sum-Product Networks (SPNs), which are a type of probabilistic graphical model used for density estimation. The paper focuses on a Bayesian approach to structure learning, which is a common topic in the machine learning subfield of Bayesian methods (cs.LG). Additionally, SPNs are often used in artificial intelligence applications (cs.AI) such as image and speech recognition (cs.CV), and can be used for data mining (cs.DM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
